  SUMMARY FINDINGS
==========================================================================================

  Top-10 hitter WAR-eq (avg of 1920s-1940s): 13.47
  Top-10 hitter WAR-eq (avg of 2000s-2020s): 10.40
  -> Top-end hitting talent appears LOWER in recent decades (+3.08)
     This likely reflects talent SPREADING (more parity), not declining ability.

  WAR-eq std dev (1920s-1940s avg): 2.41
  WAR-eq std dev (2000s-2020s avg): 2.10
  -> Talent is MORE EVENLY DISTRIBUTED in the modern era.
     The gap between stars and average players has narrowed.

  8+ WAR-eq seasons (1920s-1940s total): 300
  8+ WAR-eq seasons (2000s-2020s total): 123
  -> Fewer superstar seasons today — consistent with talent compression.

