==========================================================================================
  VERDICT
==========================================================================================

  Baseball talent is becoming MORE EVENLY DISTRIBUTED.
  The talent pool is deeper, making it harder for individuals to stand out.
  The top-end WAR-eq numbers have declined as the average quality of play
  has risen — the classic 'Stephen Jay Gould' theory of vanishing .400 hitters.


